<br>
But, I think you need to pay closer attention to the monks you're around, their gear, and their levels.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Monks dont have the same bandage cap as we do<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Monks have the EXACT SAME BANDAGE CAP AS YOU. Until level 51.<br>
<br>
50 percent.<br>
<br>
So if you're hanging around with monks that bandage more than 50 percent, they are over level 51.<br>
<br>
Warriors BW cap goes past 200 at a later level than monks (I forget what that is, but it's in the FAQ here). BUT, that's offset in the Alternate Advancement abilities where warriors get IMPROVED bind wounds (and will likely get an improvement to the improved bind wounds in PoP). Warriors with their AA's spent in bandaging will seriously outbandage monks. Like that's really a big deal, but ... point is ... you will eventually bandage much better than the monks you hang out with.<br>
<br>
Anyways, it sounds like you really have problems with monks class specific abilities.<br>
<br>
Seriously, if you WANT to MEND, if you WANT to Feign Death, if you WANT to do all these things monks do, play a monk. <br>
<br>
ALSO, the ONLY monks to have regen are IKSAR. Human monks have no added hit point regeneration at all. They're the same as everyone else. So if you want to have amazing hit point regeneration while you mend and feign death, play an Iksar monk.<br>
<br>
And remember TROLL and IKSAR warriors have the exact same regen as IKSAR MONKS. So you TOO could have had that regeneration as a warrior.<br>
<br>
You chose to play a warrior.<br>
<br>
There are things you will do in this game that a monk will NEVER do. Like wear an AC 75 breastplate. Like TAUNT a monster. Like taunt ALL the monsters in the general area. Like have the Avatar of War beat on you for an entire fight. Like breaking 5000 hit points unbuffed, and 7 to 10 thousand raid buffed (PoP's gonna have some nice HP improvements to warriors, I'd hope).<br>
<br>
You've got a lot to look forward to as a warrior. Don't get hung up on monks who feign death when they get their butt handed to them. They're just monks. You're the tank in the big badass looking armor taking the beating. It's what you do.<br>
<br>
And don't worry about soloing. Because druids and necromancers certainly solo a hundred times better than any silly monk.<br>
<br>
-Wu<br>
<br>
